```javascript
class MyPromise {
  constructor(executor) {
    this.state = 'pending';
    this.value = undefined;
    this.callbacks = []; // queued .then() handlers, in case .then() is called before settling

    const resolve = (value) => {
      if (this.state !== 'pending') return; // can only settle once — permanent transition
      this.state = 'fulfilled';
      this.value = value;
      this.callbacks.forEach(cb => cb.onFulfilled(value)); // flush anyone already waiting
    };

    const reject = (reason) => {
      if (this.state !== 'pending') return;
      this.state = 'rejected';
      this.value = reason;
      this.callbacks.forEach(cb => cb.onRejected(reason));
    };

    try {
      executor(resolve, reject); // executor runs synchronously, can call resolve/reject immediately or later
    } catch (err) {
      reject(err); // a thrown error inside the executor becomes a rejection automatically
    }
  }

  then(onFulfilled, onRejected) {
    return new MyPromise((resolve, reject) => {
      const handleFulfilled = (value) => {
        queueMicrotask(() => { // CRITICAL: defer even if already settled — .then() callbacks are never synchronous
          try {
            const result = onFulfilled ? onFulfilled(value) : value;
            resolve(result); // handles plain values; a full implementation also needs to "adopt" returned thenables here
          } catch (err) {
            reject(err);
          }
        });
      };
      const handleRejected = (reason) => {
        queueMicrotask(() => {
          try {
            if (onRejected) resolve(onRejected(reason)); // a handled rejection turns back into fulfillment
            else reject(reason); // no handler — propagate the rejection unchanged
          } catch (err) {
            reject(err);
          }
        });
      };

      if (this.state === 'fulfilled') handleFulfilled(this.value);
      else if (this.state === 'rejected') handleRejected(this.value);
      else this.callbacks.push({ onFulfilled: handleFulfilled, onRejected: handleRejected }); // still pending — queue for later
    });
  }
}
```

**The trickiest part to get right:** deferring `.then()` callbacks to a microtask **even when the Promise is already settled at the moment `.then()` is called**. It's tempting to just run the callback immediately if `this.state !== 'pending'` — but the real Promise spec guarantees callbacks are *never* invoked synchronously, even on an already-settled Promise, to keep execution order predictable (see the Promise state machine question). Forgetting `queueMicrotask` there is the single most common bug in hand-rolled Promise implementations — code that works in simple cases but produces wrong ordering the moment a settled Promise's `.then()` is mixed with other synchronous code that should logically run first.

A close second difficulty: correctly handling a `.then()` callback that returns *another* Promise (or thenable) — a complete implementation needs to recursively "adopt" that inner Promise's eventual state rather than resolving with the Promise object itself, which the simplified version above doesn't fully handle.

Common pitfall: implementing `resolve`/`reject` without the `if (this.state !== 'pending') return;` guard — without it, calling `resolve` a second time (or `reject` after an earlier `resolve`) would silently overwrite the already-settled state, violating the fundamental "a Promise settles exactly once" guarantee that downstream code relies on.

answer.ru:
```javascript
class MyPromise {
  constructor(executor) {
    this.state = 'pending';
    this.value = undefined;
    this.callbacks = []; // запланированные обработчики .then(), на случай вызова до разрешения

    const resolve = (value) => {
      if (this.state !== 'pending') return; // разрешиться можно только раз — необратимый переход
      this.state = 'fulfilled';
      this.value = value;
      this.callbacks.forEach(cb => cb.onFulfilled(value)); // сбрасываем всем, кто уже ждал
    };

    const reject = (reason) => {
      if (this.state !== 'pending') return;
      this.state = 'rejected';
      this.value = reason;
      this.callbacks.forEach(cb => cb.onRejected(reason));
    };

    try {
      executor(resolve, reject); // executor выполняется синхронно, может вызвать resolve/reject сразу или позже
    } catch (err) {
      reject(err); // брошенная ошибка внутри executor'а автоматически становится отклонением
    }
  }

  then(onFulfilled, onRejected) {
    return new MyPromise((resolve, reject) => {
      const handleFulfilled = (value) => {
        queueMicrotask(() => { // КРИТИЧНО: откладываем, даже если уже разрешён — колбэки .then() никогда не синхронны
          try {
            const result = onFulfilled ? onFulfilled(value) : value;
            resolve(result); // обрабатывает обычные значения; полная реализация должна "усваивать" возвращённые thenable здесь
          } catch (err) {
            reject(err);
          }
        });
      };
      const handleRejected = (reason) => {
        queueMicrotask(() => {
          try {
            if (onRejected) resolve(onRejected(reason)); // обработанное отклонение превращается обратно в исполнение
            else reject(reason); // обработчика нет — пропускаем отклонение без изменений
          } catch (err) {
            reject(err);
          }
        });
      };

      if (this.state === 'fulfilled') handleFulfilled(this.value);
      else if (this.state === 'rejected') handleRejected(this.value);
      else this.callbacks.push({ onFulfilled: handleFulfilled, onRejected: handleRejected }); // ещё pending — ставим в очередь
    });
